title: Stunning visuals but no audio
description: I've wanted to buy a monitor for a while and I can say for sure this one is a great starter, I use it for my ps4 and computer for school work, the only thing I was disappointed about is that there is no speakers, or at least I think there isn't, the manual was confusing and apparently you have to buy your own speaker to play audio, that's as far as my knowledge extends, either way highly recommend.

title: Solid gaming monitor for the price
description:
Pretty solid monitor for the price, it did its job for a meager $113. There are minor problems, but it was not game changing at all (no sound system, screen went black momentarily randomly). 

The only unfortunate problem I had with this product was that the screen broke very easily. No I did not punch it. I recommend you don't put any weight on it whatsoever. I don't think it came with a warranty so I am at a loss of $113
